# Optional: enables Google Drive cloud backup. Without it, the app stays fully
# local-first and the Settings → Cloud backup section shows a setup hint.
#
# Setup:
#   1. Google Cloud Console → APIs & Services → Credentials.
#   2. Create an OAuth 2.0 Client ID, application type "Web application".
#   3. Under "Authorized JavaScript origins" add each origin the app runs on,
#      e.g. http://localhost:5173 and https://lifelog-lyart.vercel.app
#   4. (OAuth consent screen) add the `.../auth/drive.file` scope; it's a
#      non-sensitive scope, so no Google app verification is required.
#   5. Copy the Client ID below. For local dev put it in `.env.local`; for
#      Vercel add it as the VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID env var and redeploy.
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
